^[Less foot traffic on the sidewalks was surprisingly nice, too. There's less stuff to look around at, but if you're with other people, you can have a conversation more easily.]

^[Yes, the noise from 4 lanes of traffic, especially at a 35 mph speed limit, is still kind of annoying while walking, but I found this wasn't as irritating as I expected.]

In these places, low-carbon retail trips would either be made by bike or e-scooter (in which case putting it a few blocks away is fine), or could be done by foot only if multiple errands can be done in one walk (e.g. by putting retail near other retail, or near bus stops).